item.summary: Vectorization: Prevent mutation of VectorPartitionDesc after being used in a hashmap key

status.description: The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are not closed can be reopened.

comments.comment: The validation might not be the slow part of this - the hash-function for this might be the culprit here.

When inserting into the hash table, the hashCode of the key was = 759386122, a few operations later the hashKey has its hashCode changed by.

 vectorPartDesc.setDataTypeInfos(nextDataTypeInfoList);

The vpd is changing its hashCode after being inserted into a hashtable, causing this particular issue.
Hmm. Cannot this also cause incorrect results? If the key is not found later.

No, right now it just duplicates the desc for each partition and makes the plan object bigger than it should be.

And takes like 300ms of compile time.
